Module kivakit.core.kernel
Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.kernel.interfaces.collection

Interface Sequence<Element>

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Indexable<Element>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BaseIndexedMap, BaseList, IndexedNameMap, MessageList, ObjectList, Stack, StringList, ValidationIssues
    public interface Sequence<Element>
    A sequence of values returned by asIterator() and asIterator(Matcher).

    Iteration

    Sequences can be iterated over by converting them to an Iterator or Iterable. Sequence does not directly extend these interfaces because some objects may already be using them for another purpose (and type erasures in particular would ensure difficulties).

    • asIterator() - This sequence as a Java Iterator
    • asIterable() - This sequence as a Java Iterable
    • asIterator(Matcher) - The sequence of values in this sequence that match the given matcher as a Java Iterator
    • asIterable(Matcher) - The sequence of values in this sequence that match the given matcher as a Java Iterable

    Finding Elements and Subsequences

    • find(Matcher) - The first matching element in this sequence
    • first() - The first element in the sequence, or null if there is none
    • head() - The same as first()
    • tail() - All elements in the sequence except the first one as a list
    • indexOfFirst(Object) - The index of the given element in this sequence
    • indexOfFirst(Matcher) - The index of the first matching element in this sequence

    Collections

    • asSet() - Converts the elements in this sequence into a set
    • asList() - Converts the elements in this sequence into a list
    • asHashCode() - A hash code for all the elements in this sequence

    Joining Sequences

    • join(String) - This sequence as a string with elements separated by the given separator
    • join(char) - This sequence as a string with elements separated by the given separator
    • join(String, Function) - The elements in this sequence converted to strings and separated by the given separator

    Checks

    Several methods allow checks on elements in this sequence:

    • isEqualTo(Sequence) - True if all elements in this sequence match all elements in the given sequence
    • anyMatch(Matcher) - True if any value in the sequence matches the given matcher
    • allMatch(Matcher) - True if all elements in the sequence matches the given matcher
    • noneMatch(Matcher) - True if no elements in the sequence matches the given matcher
